What will display in the result of the following statements?
var test=5+7;
document.write(test);

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Arithmetic Operators[/h1]

Arithmetic operators perform arithmetic functions on numbers (literals or variables). [img id="2745" width="100%"]
In the example below, the addition operator is used to determine the sum of two numbers.[code format="js" codeId="651"]var x = 10 + 5;
document.write(x);

// Outputs 15[/code]
You can add as many numbers or variables together as you want or need to.[code format="js" codeId="652"]var x = 10;
var y = x + 5 + 22 + 45 + 6548;
document.write(y);

//Outputs 6630[/code]

[h1]Multiplication[/h1]

The multiplication operator (*) multiplies one number by the other.[code format="js" codeId="653"]var x = 10 * 5;
document.write(x);

// Outputs 50[/code]

[h1]Division[/h1]

The / operator is used to perform division operations: [code format="js" codeId="654"]var x = 100 / 5;
document.write(x);

// Outputs 20[/code]

[h1]The Modulus[/h1]

Modulus (%) operator returns the division remainder (what is left over). [code format="js" codeId="655"]var myVariable = 26 % 6;

//myVariable equals 2[/code]
[note]In JavaScript, the modulus operator is used not only on integers, but also on floating point numbers.[/note]
